---

## 2. Environment Setup

- Install [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs/#installation)
- Run `poetry install`
- Fill in `.env.free` or `.env.azure` with your keys (see templates below)

---

## 3. Running the Assistant

- **Start in free mode:**
  ```bash
  MODE=free ./scripts/run.sh
  ```
- **Or start in Azure mode:**
  ```bash
  MODE=azure ./scripts/run.sh
  ```
- This launches the server, logs to `logs/`, and starts ngrok for public tunneling.

---

## 4. Endpoints

| Endpoint  | Method | Description |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| `/health` | GET    | Status check |
| `/voice`  | POST   | Audio â†’ pipeline |
| `/speak`  | POST   | Text â†’ audio reply |

---

## 5. Agent Stubs

All files in `src/agents/` are safe stub implementations. You can run/test out of the box, then BlackBox or Copilot can fill in each agent.

---

## 6. Logs

- `logs/uvicorn.log` â€” Server logs
- `logs/ngrok.log` â€” Ngrok logs
- Watch with:  
  ```bash
  tail -f logs/uvicorn.log logs/ngrok.log
  ```

---

## 7. Example Environment Files

### `.env.free`
```ini
MODE=free
WHISPER_BIN=./bin/whisper.cpp
WHISPER_MODEL=ggml-base.en.bin
ELEVEN_API_KEY=your-elevenlabs-api-key
ELEVEN_VOICE_ID=your-elevenlabs-voice-id
SQLITE_DB=./state_manager.db
NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=your-ngrok-token
```

### `.env.azure`
```ini
MODE=azure
AZURE_SPEECH_KEY=your-azure-speech-key
AZURE_SPEECH_REGION=your-azure-region
COSMOS_ENDPOINT=https://your-cosmos-account.documents.azure.com:443/
COSMOS_KEY=your-cosmos-key
COSMOS_DB=AgentDB
COSMOS_COLL=Leads
NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=your-ngrok-token
```

---

## 8. Next Steps

- Clone, fill env files, run the script, verify endpoints.
- Connect your voice client to the ngrok public URL.
- Hand off to BlackBox or Copilot for agent upgrades and integrations.

